-      "description": "Replace the fragile extractJson() markdown-fence regex parsing in OpenRouterAiProvider.java with OpenRouter's native structured output support. Add proper Jackson deserialization with a one-retry fallback.\n\nScope: Only backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/ai/provider/OpenRouterAiProvider.java and its test backend/src/test/java/com/weeklycommit/ai/provider/OpenRouterAiProviderTest.java. Do NOT modify any other files.\n\nDeliverables:\n- Remove the extractJson() method and all regex-based fence parsing\n- In callOpenRouter(), add `response_format: { type: \"json_object\" }` to the request body JSON (OpenRouter's supported mode for Claude models). This ensures the LLM returns valid JSON without fences.\n- In parseResponse(), parse the response content directly with Jackson objectMapper.readTree() — no fence extraction needed\n- Remove the extractRationale() method. Set rationale to either a \"rationale\" field extracted from the LLM's JSON response (if present), or the default string \"AI-generated suggestion\" when absent.\n- Keep the hard-coded 0.85 confidence for now (Step 9 addresses this properly)\n- Update OpenRouterAiProviderTest.java to test: valid JSON response, malformed JSON fallback to unavailable(), empty response handling, and rationale extraction from JSON payload\n- Add a one-retry fallback: if Jackson parsing fails on the response content, retry the callOpenRouter() call once with the same prompt. If second attempt also fails, return AiSuggestionResult.unavailable(). Restructure generateSuggestion() to wrap the call+parse in a retry loop.",
