-      "description": "Fix the unbounded findByOwnerUserId() call that loads ALL past commits for a user into the prompt context.\n\nScope: Only backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/ai/service/CommitDraftAssistService.java, backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/domain/repository/WeeklyCommitRepository.java, and backend/src/test/java/com/weeklycommit/ai/service/CommitDraftAssistServiceTest.java.\n\nDeliverables:\n- Add a new repository method to WeeklyCommitRepository.java: `List<WeeklyCommit> findByOwnerUserIdAndCreatedAtAfter(UUID ownerUserId, Instant cutoff)` — the WeeklyCommit entity has a `createdAt` field (Instant), so this Spring Data derived query will work.\n- In CommitDraftAssistService.assist(), replace `commitRepo.findByOwnerUserId(plan.getOwnerUserId())` with the bounded query using `Instant.now().minus(84, ChronoUnit.DAYS)` (12 weeks) as cutoff\n- Update CommitDraftAssistServiceTest.java to verify the bounded query is used (mock should expect the time-bounded call, not the unbounded one)",
