-      "title": "Add cross-encoder reranking service",
-      "description": "Add a reranking layer between Pinecone retrieval and LLM context assembly.\n\nScope: Only files in backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/ai/rag/ and test counterparts. Do NOT modify frontend or non-RAG files.\n\nDeliverables:\n- Create backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/ai/rag/RerankService.java:\n  - Interface: `List<RankedChunk> rerank(String query, List<PineconeClient.PineconeMatch> candidates, int topN)`\n  - `RankedChunk` record: `record RankedChunk(String id, double score, Map<String, Object> metadata, double rerankScore)`\n  - Default implementation uses the LLM (via AiProviderRegistry) as a batch reranker: send ALL candidate chunks in a single LLM prompt with the query, asking the LLM to return a JSON array of {chunkId, relevanceScore}. Parse scores and re-order. This is ONE LLM call, not one per chunk.\n  - Alternatively, if Cohere Rerank API is available via `ai.rerank.api-key` config property, call that instead. Fall back to LLM-based reranking if the Cohere key is absent.\n  - Include @Value(\"${ai.rerank.enabled:false}\") feature flag — DEFAULTS TO FALSE. When false, skip reranking entirely (pass-through: just truncate to top-N by Pinecone score). Teams opt-in to reranking once a Cohere API key is configured. LLM-based reranking is the last-resort fallback, not the intended production path — it adds a third LLM call per RAG query (on top of intent classification + answer generation) and can add 5-30s of latency. The intended production path is: (1) Cohere Rerank API if ai.rerank.api-key is set, (2) disabled/pass-through otherwise. LLM-based reranking exists only as a development/testing fallback when Cohere is unavailable but reranking is explicitly enabled.\n  - Include @Value(\"${ai.rerank.top-n:20}\") for configurable top-N\n  - Graceful degradation: if reranking fails for any reason, return the original candidates unchanged (truncated to topN) with a log warning\n- Modify SemanticQueryService.java:\n  - Inject RerankService. After Pinecone retrieval, call rerankService.rerank(question, matches, topN)\n  - Increase TOP_K from 40 to 80 (retrieve more candidates for the reranker to filter)\n  - Pass only the reranked top-N results to the RAG prompt context\n- Add RerankServiceTest.java: reranking re-orders chunks; feature flag disabled → pass-through; reranking failure → graceful fallback\n- Update SemanticQueryServiceTest.java to inject and mock RerankService",
