-      "title": "Add statistical predictive calibration service — backend",
-      "description": "Build a completion-rate model from historical data for predictive planning intelligence.\n\nIMPORTANT DATA MODEL NOTE: The UserWeekFact entity only stores aggregate fields: totalPlannedPoints, totalAchievedPoints, commitCount, carryForwardCount, scopeChangeCount, kingCount, and queenCount. It does NOT store per-chess-piece achievement/planned data or per-piece estimates. Therefore, per-chess-piece achievement rates and average estimates MUST be computed from WeeklyCommit data directly (which has chessPiece, estimatePoints, and outcome fields).\n\nScope: Only backend files. Do NOT modify any frontend files.\n\nDeliverables:\n- Create backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/ai/service/CalibrationService.java:\n  - CalibrationProfile getCalibration(UUID userId) — returns rolling achievement stats\n  - CalibrationProfile record contains:\n    - overallAchievementRate (double) — totalAchievedPoints / totalPlannedPoints over last 12 weeks from UserWeekFact rows\n    - Map<ChessPiece, Double> chessPieceAchievementRates — per-chess-piece calibration. Computed from WeeklyCommit data: query commits via WeeklyCommitRepository for the user's last 12 weeks (join through plan's weekStartDate or filter by createdAt). Group by chessPiece, count ACHIEVED vs total outcomes.\n    - double carryForwardProbability — carryForwardCount / commitCount from UserWeekFact rows\n    - int weeksOfData — number of UserWeekFact rows found\n    - Map<ChessPiece, Double> avgEstimateByPiece — average estimatePoints per chess piece from WeeklyCommit data\n    - confidenceTier (enum CalibrationConfidenceTier: HIGH, MEDIUM, LOW, INSUFFICIENT) — based on weeksOfData (<8 = INSUFFICIENT, 8-15 = LOW, 15-30 = MEDIUM, 30+ = HIGH). Named CalibrationConfidenceTier to avoid collision with the evidence-based ConfidenceTier from Step 9.\n  - Inject both UserWeekFactRepository and WeeklyCommitRepository\n  - Query UserWeekFactRepository.findByUserIdAndWeekStartBetween() for aggregate stats\n  - Add a new repository method to WeeklyCommitRepository: a native SQL @Query that finds commits by ownerUserId where the commit's plan has weekStartDate within a date range. IMPORTANT: WeeklyCommit.planId is a raw UUID column, NOT a @ManyToOne JPA relationship, so JPQL JOIN ... ON will not compile. Use a native query instead: `@Query(value = \"SELECT c.* FROM weekly_commit c JOIN weekly_plan p ON c.plan_id = p.id WHERE c.owner_user_id = :userId AND p.week_start_date >= :from AND p.week_start_date <= :to\", nativeQuery = true)`. The return type is still List<WeeklyCommit> since Spring Data maps native results back to the entity.\n  - Returns CalibrationProfile.insufficient() when <8 weeks of data\n- Create backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/ai/dto/CalibrationProfileResponse.java — API response DTO\n- Add endpoint to AiController.java: GET /api/ai/calibration/{userId} → returns CalibrationProfileResponse\n- Add backend/src/test/java/com/weeklycommit/ai/service/CalibrationServiceTest.java:\n  - Test: 12 weeks of data produces valid rates\n  - Test: <8 weeks returns insufficient\n  - Test: per-chess-piece rates computed correctly (mock both UserWeekFactRepository and WeeklyCommitRepository)\n  - Test: carry-forward probability matches historical frequency",
