-      "description": "Replace the hard-coded 0.85 confidence with structured evidence-based tiers. Integrate calibration data into AI prompts.\n\nScope: Only backend files in backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/ai/. Do NOT modify frontend files.\n\nDeliverables:\n- Create backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/ai/evidence/ConfidenceTierCalculator.java:\n  - ConfidenceTier calculate(List<PineconeClient.PineconeMatch> matches) — simplified signature using only Pinecone matches for RAG context\n  - Enum ConfidenceTier { HIGH, MEDIUM, LOW, INSUFFICIENT } with display labels\n  - Logic: HIGH ≥3 matches >0.8; MEDIUM ≥1 match >0.8 or ≥5 matches >0.5; LOW only matches <0.5; INSUFFICIENT no matches\n  - Overloaded method accepting StructuredEvidence for richer tier calculation\n  - Pure computation — no external calls\n- Modify OpenRouterAiProvider.java:\n  - In parseResponse(), attempt to read a \"confidence\" field from the LLM's JSON response. If present and between 0.0-1.0, use it. If absent or out of range, use 0.5 as default. This replaces the hard-coded 0.85.\n- Modify SemanticQueryService.java:\n  - Inject ConfidenceTierCalculator. After reranking, compute ConfidenceTier from the reranked matches.\n  - Add a confidenceTier field to RagQueryResult record. Update the record definition, the query() method return, and the unavailable() factory method.\n- Modify RagQueryResponse.java DTO: add `String confidenceTier` field. Update AiController.ragQuery() to map result.confidenceTier().name() into the response.\n- Modify CommitDraftAssistService.java: Inject CalibrationService and include CalibrationProfile in additionalContext map as \"calibration\" (serialized).\n- Modify RiskDetectionService.java: Inject CalibrationService and include calibration data in detectAiRiskSignals() method's additionalContext.\n- Add ConfidenceTierCalculatorTest.java: test all 4 tier conditions\n- Update SemanticQueryServiceTest.java to inject and mock ConfidenceTierCalculator",
