-      "title": "Add typed workflow orchestration — risk→what-if→recommendation pipeline (backend)",
-      "description": "Wire RiskDetectionService and WhatIfService into a typed workflow that produces actionable recommendations when risks are detected.\n\nScope: Only backend files in backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/ai/. Do NOT modify frontend files.\n\nDeliverables:\n- Create backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/ai/service/PlanRecommendationService.java:\n  - List<PlanRecommendation> generateRecommendations(UUID planId, UUID userId) — userId needed for risk signal access and WhatIfRequest\n  - PlanRecommendation record: record PlanRecommendation(UUID suggestionId, String riskType, String description, String suggestedAction, WhatIfResponse whatIfResult, String narrative, ConfidenceTier confidence). The suggestionId field is the primary key of the persisted AiSuggestion row for this recommendation (see persistence step below). It is required so the frontend can post feedback via AiFeedbackButtons and track per-recommendation dismissal.\n  - Two public methods:\n    a. List<PlanRecommendation> generateAndPersistRecommendations(UUID planId, UUID userId) — the generation method. Follows the same delete-then-regenerate pattern as RiskDetectionService.detectAndStoreRiskSignals():\n       1. Delete any existing PLAN_RECOMMENDATION rows for this plan: suggestionRepo.findByPlanIdAndSuggestionType(planId, \"PLAN_RECOMMENDATION\") → suggestionRepo.deleteAll(existing).\n       2. Call RiskDetectionService.getRiskSignals(planId, userId) to get current risk signals. If none stored, call detectAndStoreRiskSignalsById(planId) first.\n       3. For OVERCOMMIT/UNDERCOMMIT: identify lowest-priority commit (PAWN first) via WeeklyCommitRepository.findByPlanIdOrderByPriorityOrder(), call WhatIfService.simulate(WhatIfRequest) with REMOVE_COMMIT mutation.\n       4. For REPEATED_CARRY_FORWARD: call CalibrationService for carry-forward probability, call WhatIfService to simulate modifying the commit (reduce estimate).\n       5. Assemble PlanRecommendation objects with what-if narrative.\n       6. Persist each PlanRecommendation as an AiSuggestion row via AiSuggestionService.storeSuggestion() with suggestionType \"PLAN_RECOMMENDATION\". Set the prompt to the serialized risk+calibration context and the suggestionPayload to the JSON-serialized recommendation. The returned AiSuggestion.getId() becomes the PlanRecommendation.suggestionId.\n       7. Return empty list when no risks detected.\n    b. List<PlanRecommendation> getRecommendations(UUID planId) — the retrieval method. Reads persisted PLAN_RECOMMENDATION rows from AiSuggestionRepository.findByPlanIdAndSuggestionType(planId, \"PLAN_RECOMMENDATION\"), deserializes each row's suggestionPayload back into PlanRecommendation (with the row's id as suggestionId). Returns stable IDs across repeated calls — no regeneration, no new rows.\n  - The GET endpoint calls getRecommendations() (read-only). A separate POST endpoint or an explicit ?refresh=true query param triggers generateAndPersistRecommendations(). This ensures the suggestionId is stable across page loads and refetches, making localStorage-based dismissal and AiFeedbackButtons reliable.\n  - Graceful degradation: if WhatIfService or CalibrationService fails, return risk signal without recommendation (still persisted as a partial AiSuggestion so it gets a suggestionId).\n  - Inject WeeklyCommitRepository to load commits for the plan.\n  - Inject AiSuggestionService for persisting recommendation audit rows.\n- Create backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/ai/dto/PlanRecommendationResponse.java — API response DTO. Must include a UUID suggestionId field so the frontend can reference it for AiFeedbackButtons and per-recommendation dismissal.\n- Add endpoints to AiController.java:\n  - GET /api/ai/plans/{planId}/recommendations with X-Actor-User-Id header → returns List<PlanRecommendationResponse> by reading persisted rows (stable IDs, no regeneration).\n  - POST /api/ai/plans/{planId}/recommendations/refresh with X-Actor-User-Id header → triggers generateAndPersistRecommendations(), deletes stale rows, persists fresh ones, returns the new list. Called when the plan changes or the user explicitly requests a refresh.\n- Add PlanRecommendationServiceTest.java: OVERCOMMIT produces recommendation; no risks → empty; WhatIfService failure → risk without recommendation; multiple risks → multiple recommendations; getRecommendations returns stable IDs from persisted rows without regeneration; generateAndPersistRecommendations deletes stale rows before persisting new ones",
